This paper discusses collaboration in online information seeking, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper focuses on information seeking and retrieval systems. The second likely category is cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper discusses how people can help each other find information in networked environments. The third likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper discusses natural language processing and how it can be used to facilitate collaboration. The fourth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper discusses how people can collaborate in online networks. The fifth likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the social implications of online collaboration.
